# --- GitHub Linguist language-detection overrides ---
#
# The repo is Rust. The mountain of *.m files are Power Query M test
# fixtures, but Linguist has no "Power Query M" language and guesses
# them as MATLAB / Wolfram / Objective-C by the shared .m extension.
# That made the language bar read "35% Wolfram" — nonsense. Reclassify
# the M files so the bar reflects what the project actually is.

# The Oracle differential-test corpus: 1,500+ machine-extracted cases
# plus the generated outputs. Not authored source — exclude from stats.
Oracle/cases/**          linguist-generated
Oracle/coverage/*.tsv    linguist-generated
Oracle/coverage/*.md     linguist-generated
Oracle/coverage/*.m      linguist-generated

# The hand-written Oracle catalog and helper queries are test-fixture
# data, not library source — vendor them so they don't dominate the bar.
Oracle/*.m               linguist-vendored

# Example M queries and tool fixtures are documentation/data, not the
# implementation. Mark as data so they don't count as code.
examples/**/*.m              linguist-vendored
tools/explain/test_cases/**  linguist-vendored
tools/png-decoder/m/**       linguist-vendored

# Anything Linguist still detects as MATLAB/Wolfram/Objective-C from a
# .m extension is Power Query M here. There's no Linguist alias for it,
# so the classifications above (generated/vendored) are how we keep the
# bar honest. Detect remaining *.m as plain text rather than a wrong
# language.
*.m text

# The vendored odbc-api fork is third-party — exclude from stats.
vendor/**                linguist-vendored
